President Barack Obama issued a proclamation declaring June 14 as Flag Day and the week beginning June 10 as National Flag Week. He emphasized the significance of the American flag as a symbol of liberty, democracy, and freedom. The proclamation called for the display of the flag on all Federal Government buildings and encouraged all Americans to observe Flag Day and National Flag Week by displaying the flag. Additionally, President Obama urged the public to honor America and celebrate its heritage through public gatherings and activities, as well as recite the Pledge of Allegiance.